                "HPGE",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A coaxial n-type HPGe detector, of 109%",
                "relative efficiency. Additionally, a CeBr detector",
                "was fixed at a backward angle of -135 degree in order",
                "to provide a consistency check throughout the",
                "experiment and monitor for any drifting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three different types of nitrogen implanted targets",
                "with backings of Mo, Ta, and W to reduce systematic",
                "uncertainties. The targets were produced with the 5",
                "MV Sta. Ana accelerator at the University of Notre",
                "Dame Nuclear Science Laboratory. The Ta, Mo, and W",
                "targets were found to have nitrogen contents of",
                "21.3+-1.3, 13.1+-0.7, and 13.4+-0.5*10**17 atoms/cm2,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The lifetimes have been determined with the Doppler-",
                "Shift Attenuation Method (DSAM) with three separate,",
                "nitrogen-implanted targets with Mo, Ta, and W backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
